"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The 'healthy' column is being added to the DataFrame in the transform method of the HealthyAttributeAdder class, but it is included in the categorical features for OneHotEncoder. This violates the scikit-learn guideline that states that the features passed to OneHotEncoder should not include newly created features that are not part of the original DataFrame. The 'healthy' column should be excluded from the categorical features list.\", \"patch\": \"35c35\\n< cat_col = ['sex', 'smoker', 'region', 'healthy']\\n---\\n> cat_col = ['sex', 'smoker', 'region']\\n\"}"